definition.value: A glucotriose consisting of three alpha-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->6) and (1->2) glycosidic bonds.
A disaccharide phosphate consisting of a 6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannopyranose residue and a alpha-D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.
A glucotriose that is D-glucopyranose in which the hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4 have each been converted to the corresponding alpha-D-glucopyranosyl derivative.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A glucotriose consisting of beta-D-glucopyranose, alpha-D-glucopyranose and D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by (1->2) glycosidic bonds.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactopyranosyl, 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-2-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucopyranosyl and 2-acetamido-2-deoxygalactitol residues linked together in sequence by (1->3) glycosidic bonds.
